cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with image retrieval benchmarking and evaluates different types of methods ranging from local-feature-based to modern CNN based methods. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper introduces new protocols for fair comparison between different methods and evaluates the state-of-the-art methods on the new benchmark. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with large scale image retrieval benchmarking and introduces new challenging queries and a new set of distractors. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper evaluates different types of methods and discusses the best results achieved by taking the best of the two worlds. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): Although less likely, this paper could also belong to this sub-category as it deals with the creation of new annotations for the datasets and the reliability of the ground truth.
